<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer12457924777005011984">The superbly crafted stories collected in Alistair MacLeod’s <i>As Birds Bring Forth the Sun and Other Stories</i> depict men and women acting out their “own peculiar mortality” against the haunting landscape of Cape Breton Island. In a voice at once elegiac and life-affirming, MacLeod describes a vital present inhabited by the unquiet spirits of a Highland past, invoking memory </span>
  <span id="freeText12457924777005011984" style="display:none">The superbly crafted stories collected in Alistair MacLeod’s <i>As Birds Bring Forth the Sun and Other Stories</i> depict men and women acting out their “own peculiar mortality” against the haunting landscape of Cape Breton Island. In a voice at once elegiac and life-affirming, MacLeod describes a vital present inhabited by the unquiet spirits of a Highland past, invoking memory and myth to celebrate the continuity of the generations even in the midst of unremitting change.<br /><br />His second collection, <i>As Birds Bring Forth the Sun and Other Stories</i> confirms MacLeod’s international reputation as a storyteller of rare talent and inspiration.<br /><br /><br /><i>From the Trade Paperback edition.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="12457924777005011984" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

